Working example can be found here (world read access):
/afs/cern.ch/work/y/ylevinse/python27

You can use this by sourcing the activate script:
$ /afs/cern.ch/work/y/ylevinse/python27/bin/activate
$ python

..INSTALLATION..
The basic setup is:

./build

This should in principle build all needed packages..

If you are not Yngve you should at the moment set the PREFIX variable:

PREFIX=$HOME/python27 ./build
